This represents a burden on many families, which, under Ms. Warren’s plan, would disappear completely for 75 percent of them, and at least partially for 95 percent.
No one can accuse Ms. Warren of thinking small.
Ms. Warren proposes a wealth tax to cover the cost, the proceeds of which would then not be available for alternative, possibly more progressive uses.
Other Democrats have, quite properly, raised feasibility concerns about Ms. Warren’s plan.
Such issues are hardest for students and families of color, as Ms. Warren correctly emphasized.